headlines.description: — LaMelo Ball scored 31 points, hitting seven 3-pointers, and the Charlotte Hornets used a 24-0 third period run to battle back and beat the Indiana Pacers 123-122 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ball scores 31 to rally Hornets past Pacers 123-122

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine can still score in bunches when needed.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine scores 34 points, Bulls beat Pistons 94-88 in opener

events.name: Boston Celtics at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — The New York Knicks never could contain Jaylen Brown and on the last play of regulation completely lost track of Marcus Smart.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks withstand Brown's 46, outlast Celtics 138-134 in 2 OT

headlines.description: — The Washington Wizards have a new coach and a new supporting cast around Bradley Beal, the superstar they are hoping will lead the franchise out of its enduring doldrums.
headlines.shortLinkText: Beal has 23, Wizards top Raptors 98-83, spoil Toronto return

headlines.description: — Ja Morant had 37 points and six assists, De’Anthony Melton added 20 points and the Memphis Grizzlies pulled away in the fourth for a 132-121 victory over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Wednesday night in the opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant, Melton lead Grizzlies to opening win over Cavs

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards energized the first full-size home crowd of his nascent career with 29 points in 31 minutes for the Minnesota Timberwolves, who cruised to a 124-106 victory over the Houston Rockets to start the season on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards energizes Wolves in opening 124-106 win over Rockets

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid and those members of the Philadelphia 76ers who made the trip to New Orleans for their regular-season opener looked unfazed by the absence of Ben Simmons and unaffected by the drama surrounding the disgruntled All-Star guard.
headlines.shortLinkText: Joel Embiid, Furkan Korkmaz help 76ers beat Pelicans 117-97

events.name: Orlando Magic at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — San Antonio coach Gregg Popovich has loosened things up on the court after years of structure and it resulted in another successful opener for the Spurs.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vassell, Walker lead balanced Spurs past Magic, 123-97

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — The Utah Jazz opened a new season with a typical dominant defensive performance.
— Nikola Jokic was up to his old tricks Wednesday night, scoring on a crafty array of hook shots, 3-pointers and flat-footed jumpers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic scores 27 points, Nuggets beat Suns 110-98

events.name: Sacramento Kings at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — The Sacramento Kings will be in a good place this season if Harrison Barnes can consistently shoot like he did in the season opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barnes has 36 and the Kings spoil Portland's opener 124-121
